```

### Code Quality
- Run `ruff check` and `ruff format` before commits
- Run `mypy` for type checking
- All tests must pass before merging
- Review code for adherence to Clean Architecture boundaries

## Docker Deployment

```dockerfile
FROM python:3.11-slim

WORKDIR /app
COPY pyproject.toml .
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir .
COPY src/ src/
COPY alembic/ alembic/
COPY alembic.ini .

CMD ["uvicorn", "src.main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000"]
```

Use `docker-compose.yml` for local development with PostgreSQL:

```yaml
services:
  api:
    build: ./backend
    ports:
      - "8000:8000"
    environment:
      - DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://user:pass@db:5432/app
    depends_on:
      - db
  db:
    image: postgres:16
    environment:
      POSTGRES_USER: user
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: pass
      POSTGRES_DB: app
    ports:
      - "5432:5432"
    volumes:
      - pgdata:/var/lib/postgresql/data

volumes:
  pgdata:
```

## Definition of Done (Backend)

A backend change is complete when:
- [ ] All new code has type annotations
- [ ] Unit tests cover happy path, error cases, and edge cases
- [ ] Test coverage meets 90% threshold
- [ ] Pydantic schemas validate all API inputs
